  "text": "Pinonaldehyde has been observed from the low-NO x photooxidation of α-pinene previously; however, it is typically assigned as a product of RO 2 + RO 2 chemistry [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . In the present set of experiments, the chemistry is overwhelmingly dominated by RO 2 + HO 2 (i.e. low α-pinene concentration and relatively high HO 2 concentration). This is confirmed by the photooxidation products observed. The two main reaction channels for alkyl peroxy radicals with other RO 2 are:",
